The Expo on Democracy and Open Government is an event that highlights Indian innovations in strengthening democracy through technology, citizen empowerment, and accountability. It focuses on themes such as transparency, participation, government responsiveness, and political accountability. The event also marks the launch of the United States-India Open Government Dialogue. Exhibitors and roundtable participants include organizations fighting against government corruption, promoting accountability and transparency, working on urban infrastructure and citizen engagement, ending hunger, empowering women in local village councils, and enabling citizens to track legislative and policy reforms.